def: The surrounding frame into which a door shuts.
A device for pulling off boots.
A fixed point or station; a basis or fundamental principle; aposition from which objects or principles are viewed, and accordingto which they are compared and judged.
To any extent; in any degree; at all.You are not to go loose any longer. Shak.Before you go any farther. Steele.
To cause to be no longer a vessel; to empty. [Obs.] Ford.
To bring forth young, as a cat; to kitten; to litter. [Prov.Eng. & Scot.]
